x4codes.hlp: Atomic Energy Research Establishment (AERE), Harwell, United Kingdom

x4freetext: The 5 MV Van de Graaff was used. The
best time resolution for the neutron groups being 4 ns.
Neutron yield was monitored either by a long
counter or by a neutron discriminating scintillation
counter using a small stylbene crystal. The angular
resolution of the neutron counter was negligibly
small because the flight path was from 1.5 to 3.5 m
The scintillation counter was a 5.08 cm
diameter by 5.08 cm long Nuclear Enterprise N.E.213
liquid phosphor used with an R.C.A. 7264 or E.M.I.
The targets of B-10 were laid down directly on 0.05 cm.
Tungsten backings in the Harwell electromagnetic
separator. The deposits had masses of 75 mu-g/cm2 and
400 mu-g/cm2. For 1.2 MeV deuteron bombarding energy
target thickness was about 25 keV. Errors arising from
target thickness considerations were estimated to be
Errors in the relative intensities arising from
uncertainty in the efficiency correction were less than
10% within any one angular distribution, and less than
